tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  26,208,"I did not destroy any nation except they were warned by sending messengers to them and revealing books."
  26,210,"The satans did not come down with this Qur’ān upon the heart of Muhammad (peace be upon him);"
  26,211,"it is permissible that they come down with it onto his heart. They are not even capable of doing that."
  26,217,"And place your reliance in all your affairs upon the Almighty who takes retribution from His enemies and is merciful to whoever repents to Him from them."